Recommended Mitigations
Web Server level:

Disable WebDAV and direct PUT handling — let only the API handle PUT
Enforce HTTPS end-to-end (client → web server → API server)
Validate and forward Authorization headers intact

API Server level:

✅ Authenticate (you have this)
✅ Authorize (you have this)
➕ Add ownership checks — not just "is user logged in" but "does this user own this resource"
➕ Whitelist allowed fields — prevent mass assignment attacks
➕ Rate limiting on PUT endpoints
➕ Use idempotency keys to prevent replay attacks

