WebDAV is an extension of HTTP that allows clients to not just read web content, but also create, edit, move, delete, and manage files on a remote web server — essentially turning a web server into a shared file system over HTTP.

How It Extends HTTP
Standard HTTP has:
GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, HEAD
WebDAV adds extra methods:
WebDAV MethodWhat It DoesPROPFINDList files/folders and their metadataPROPPATCHChange file propertiesMKCOLCreate a new directory/collectionCOPYCopy a file on the serverMOVEMove or rename a fileLOCKLock a file so others can't edit itUNLOCKRelease the lock

Real World Analogy

Think of it like Google Drive or Dropbox, but built directly on top of a web server using HTTP methods — no special app needed, just HTTP.


Where You've Seen WebDAV (Without Knowing It)

Microsoft SharePoint — uses WebDAV under the hood
Windows "Map Network Drive" via HTTP URL
macOS Finder → Connect to Server → http://...
Subversion (SVN) — early versions used WebDAV
Older CMS systems like Joomla, Drupal file managers


Why It's a Security Risk
Since WebDAV allows file uploads and management, if left enabled on a web server:
Attacker sends:
PUT /shell.php HTTP/1.1        ← Upload a malicious PHP file
Host: vulnerable-server.com
Content-Type: text/plain

<?php system($_GET['cmd']); ?>
Then visits:
https://vulnerable-server.com/shell.php?cmd=whoami
→ Full Remote Code Execution (RCE) on the server!

Risk Summary
WebDAV Enabled on Web Server
        │
        ├── Upload .php / .jsp / .asp shell
        ├── Overwrite existing application files
        ├── Browse directory structure (PROPFIND)
        ├── Move/Delete critical files
        └── Full server compromise

How to Check If WebDAV is Enabled
bash# Send an OPTIONS request to see allowed methods
curl -X OPTIONS http://yourserver.com/ -i

# If response includes these → WebDAV is ON ⚠️
# Allow: GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, PROPFIND, MKCOL, COPY, MOVE, LOCK

How to Disable WebDAV
Apache:
apache# Disable WebDAV modules
# Comment out or remove from httpd.conf:
# LoadModule dav_module modules/mod_dav.so
# LoadModule dav_fs_module modules/mod_dav_fs.so
Nginx:
nginx# Nginx doesn't support WebDAV by default
# If the dav module is compiled in, don't include:
# dav_methods PUT DELETE MKCOL COPY MOVE;
IIS (Windows):
IIS Manager → Select Site → WebDAV Authoring Rules
→ Disable WebDAV

